OL,3,C'Addiction is addiction - no one sets
OL,4,Cout to be an addict'
OL,6,FOne of the things I have learned in
OL,7,Fthe short time that I've been talking
OL,8,Fto people for UTV's podcast 'Going the
OL,9,FExtra Mile', is the importance of
OL,10,Flived experience.
OL,12,FIt has turned into such a cliched term
OL,13,Fin many respects but for most of the
OL,14,Fpeople I've spoken to, it is their own
OL,15,Fpast experience, something which they
OL,16,Fhave gone through, something that they
OL,17,Fhave survived that gives them their
OL,18,Fpassion, their motivation and the
OL,19,Fdesire to help others.
