OL,3,C'Addiction is addiction - no one sets
OL,4,Cout to be an addict'
OL,6,F"Never did I think I would end up an
OL,7,Faddict. I crossed the line. I hadn't
OL,8,Feven realised that I crossed the line
OL,9,Funtil I had responsibilities like
OL,10,Fchildren. I realised there was a
OL,11,Fproblem. Alcohol is what I was
OL,12,Faddicted to. It got to the stage where
OL,13,FI lost complete control," Emma said.
OL,15,FThe effects of addiction are
OL,16,Funiversal. Emma is at pains to
OL,17,Femphasise that there is not one addict
OL,18,Fstereotype. It doesn't matter where
OL,19,Fyou come from, what your job is, how
OL,20,Fyou were educated, anyone can end up
OL,21,Fliving with addiction.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/6
