OL,3,C'Addiction is addiction - no one sets
OL,4,Cout to be an addict'
OL,6,F"Addiction is addiction. No one sets
OL,7,Fout to be an addict. I know I didn't.
OL,8,FI didn't want to be drinking in the
OL,9,Fmorning to get up and go to work or
OL,10,Fbring my children to school. I have
OL,11,Fmet some very professional people in
OL,12,Frecovery as well, even doctors and
OL,13,Fnurses, lawyers and barristers," she
OL,14,Fadded.
OL,16,F"There's loads of them in there as
OL,17,Fwell, just as much as the homeless
OL,18,Fperson on the street. Those two minds
OL,19,Fcan come together. They can meet on
OL,20,Fone thing and that's the state of mind
OL,21,Fof an addict."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/6
